From 211afe68858c1b959f131b55455fe33e38e79e6d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sergio Andreozzi <digitalities@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 09:32:53 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/8] traffic-control, network, point-to-point, csma: Add L2
 framing overhead awareness

Adds NetDevice::GetL2OverheadBytes() virtual that exposes per-packet
L2 framing overhead, plus QueueDisc::ChargeBytes() helper and
QueueDisc::L2OverheadBytes attribute that resolve the overhead at
qdisc accounting time.

NetDevice::GetL2OverheadBytes() default returns 0, so existing
NetDevice subclasses are unaffected. PointToPointNetDevice overrides
to return PppHeader().GetSerializedSize() (2 bytes). CsmaNetDevice
overrides to return EthernetHeader().GetSerializedSize() (14 bytes).
WifiNetDevice and LteNetDevice keep the default 0 (per-packet
framing varies, not summarisable as a scalar).

QueueDisc::ChargeBytes(item) returns item->GetSize() plus the
resolved L2 overhead. The overhead source is QueueDisc's
L2OverheadBytes attribute when set explicitly, otherwise the
underlying NetDevice's GetL2OverheadBytes() via
m_devQueueIface->GetDevice(), otherwise 0. The attribute defaults
to UINT32_MAX (auto-detect from netdev), preserving pre-patch
behaviour bit-for-bit on every NetDevice that does not override.

This is the API foundation. The four wire-byte-accounting qdiscs
(FqCoDel, FqCobalt, FqPie, Tbf) will swap their direct
item->GetSize() calls for ChargeBytes(item) in a follow-up commit
on the same MR, alongside updates to the affected test
expected-values.

