Subject: [PATCH 2/8] network: Add NetDeviceQueueInterface::GetDevice()
 accessor

NetDeviceQueueInterface exposes GetTxQueue(i) and GetNTxQueues() but
not the underlying NetDevice it is aggregated to. Callers that need
the device (typically queue discs reading per-NetDevice properties at
accounting time) must currently use GetObject<NetDevice>() on the
interface, which works because the NetDevice is aggregated in
NotifyNewAggregate but is unfamiliar at the call site.

Adds Ptr<NetDevice> NetDeviceQueueInterface::GetDevice() const that
returns GetObject<NetDevice>(). No caching; the lookup is the same as
the existing call path that NotifyNewAggregate uses on line 90 of the
.cc to populate per-NetDeviceQueue m_device fields.

Adds a focused regression test that installs a SimpleNetDevice on a
node, fetches the aggregated NetDeviceQueueInterface, and asserts
GetDevice() returns the same NetDevice (pointer equality) and agrees
with GetObject<NetDevice>().

