From a5eac1074f66b66eb1054d44f399a4bc0ed05b17 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sergio Andreozzi <digitalities@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 18:58:18 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 6/8] traffic-control: FqCoDelQueueDisc charges wire bytes via
 QueueDisc::ChargeBytes

The DRR deficit decrement at the rate-accounting site swaps
item->GetSize() for QueueDisc::ChargeBytes(item), so per-packet
deficit consumption tracks wire bytes rather than IP-layer bytes.
Existing fq-codel-queue-disc test runs over zero-overhead
constructed Ipv4QueueDiscItem instances, so the test is unaffected.

The drop-batch loop in FqCoDelDrop continues to count item->GetSize()
because its threshold is derived from MaxSize, which is also expressed
in IP-layer bytes; mixing wire and IP bytes there would skew the
loop's stop condition.

Assisted-by: Claude Code (Anthropic, claude-opus-4-7)
